'''Ana Diez''' (born 1957) is a [[Spain|Spanish]] director and screenwriter, who born in Tudela, Navarra. She spent time in Mexico where she received her degree in cinema. One of her best-known films is ''Ander eta Yul'', which was in the [[Basque language]]. She has been referred to as "the first woman director in the New Basque Cinema."<ref name="Martí-Olivella2003">{{cite book |author=Jaume Martí-Olivella |title=Basque Cinema: An Introduction |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=76Pm0V7BW4cC |year=2003 |publisher=University of Nevada Press |isbn=978-1-877802-19-5}}</ref> She received the [[Goya Award for Best New Director]] for the film.<ref name="Schwartz2008">{{cite book |author=Ronald Schwartz |title=Great Spanish Films Since 1950 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PmMYAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA302 |date=5 September 2008 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=978-1-4616-9661-2 |pages=302–}}</ref>

