'''Natalya Durova''' (1934-2007) was a Russian/Soviet circus performer and animal trainer.<ref name="Circus">{{cite web|url=http://www.russia-ic.com/news/show/5255/#.Vy6ACuT2aM8 |title=Circus Legend Natalya Durova Passed Away :: Russia-InfoCentre |publisher=Russia-ic.com |date=2007-11-27 |accessdate=2016-05-08}}</ref> She first began performing in the circus at the age of four.<ref name="Circus"/> During [[World War II]] she performed for the [[Red Army]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themoscowtimes.com/news/article/durov-theater-celebrates-two-milestones/231477.html |title=Durov Theater Celebrates Two Milestones &#124; News |publisher=The Moscow Times |date=2004-04-20 |accessdate=2016-05-08}}</ref> She was given the Guards' badge by [[G.K. Zhukov]] when she was nine years old.<ref name="Circus"/> She also directed the Durov Animal Theatre.<ref>{{cite web|author=Clara Ferreira-Marques |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/carnival-of-the-animals/article1021537/ |title=Carnival of the animals |publisher=The Globe and Mail |date= |accessdate=2016-05-08}}</ref> She was a [[People's Artist of the USSR]] and a [[People’s Artist of the RSFSR|People's Artist of the RSFSR]].<ref name="Circus"/>
