'''Richard Baerwald''' (1867&ndash;1929) was a [[Germany|German]] academic [[psychologist]], in [[Berlin]].  Towards the end of his life he became interested in [[parapsychology]] and [[occultism]] (as it was interpreted at the period). He edited the ''Zeitschrift für Kritischen Okkultismus'' from 1926 to 1928.<ref>Kurtz, Paul. (1985). ''A Skeptic's Handbook of Parapsychology''. Prometheus Books. p. 487. {{ISBN|0-87975-300-5}}</ref>

